equest` struct in `types.go`\n- [ ] **2.11** Define `Config` struct in `server.go` - server configuration with port, graceful shutdown timeout\n- [ ] **2.12** Define `Server` struct in `server.go` - HTTP server wrapper\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Service Interface Implementation\n\n- [ ] **3.1** Define `WorkloadManager` interface in `service.go`\n- [ ] **3.2** Implement `workloadManagerImpl` struct in `service.go`\n- [ ] **3.3** Implement `NewWorkloadManager` constructor function\n- [ ] **3.4** Implement `CreateAgentRuntime` method\n- [ ] **3.5** Implement `GetAgentRuntime` method\n- [ ] **3.6** Implement `ListAgentRuntimes` method with labelSelector support\n- [ ] **3.7** Implement `UpdateAgentRuntime` method\n- [ ] **3.8** Implement `DeleteAgentRuntime` method\n- [ ] **3.9** Implement `GetAgentRuntimeStatus` method\n- [ ] **3.10** Implement `PatchAgentRuntimeStatus` method\n- [ ] **3.11** Implement `WatchAgentRuntimes` method (for watch=true queries)\n- [ ] **3.12** Implement `CreateCodeInterpreter` method\n- [ ] **3.13** Implement `GetCodeInterpreter` method\n- [ ] **3.14** Implement `ListCodeInterpreters` method with labelSelector support\n- [ ] **3.15** Implement `UpdateCodeInterpreter` method\n- [ ] **3.16** Implement `DeleteCodeInterpreter` method\n- [ ] **3.17** Implement `GetCodeInterpreterStatus` method\n- [ ] **3.18** Implement `PatchCodeInterpreterStatus` method\n- [ ] **3.19** Implement `WatchCodeInterpreters` method\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: Kubernetes Client Integration\n\n- [ ] **4.1** Implement `NewK8sClient` function in `client.go` - create Kubernetes clientset from kubeconfig\n- [ ] **4.2** Implement `NewInClusterClient` function in `client.go` - create client for in-cluster mode\n- [ ] **4.3** Implement `NewClientset` function in `client.go` - create typed clientset for AgentCube CRDs\n- [ ] **4.4** Implement `NewInformerFactory` function in `client.go` - create SharedInformerFactory\n- [ ] **4.5** Implement `RegisterInformers` method in `server.go` - register AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter informers\n- [ ] **4.6** Implement `StartInformers` method in `server.go` - start informers and wait for cache sync\n- [ ] **4.7** Implement client cleanup in `Close` method - close HTTP clients without goroutine leaks\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: HTTP Handlers\n\n- [ ] **5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agentruntime.go`\n- [ ] **5.2** Implement `HandleCreateAgentRuntime` handler - POST /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes\n- [ ] **5.3** Implement `HandleGetAgentRuntime` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}\n- [ ] **5.4** Implement `HandleListAgentRuntimes` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes (with labelSelector, watch)\n- [ ] **5.5** Implement `HandleUpdateAgentRuntime` handler - PUT /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}\n- [ ] **5.6** Implement `HandleDeleteAgentRuntime` handler - DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}\n- [ ] **5.7** Implement `HandleGetAgentRuntimeStatus` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}/status\n- [ ] **5.8** Implement `HandlePatchAgentRuntimeStatus` handler - PATCH /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}/status\n- [ ] **5.9** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/codeinterpreter.go`\n- [ ] **5.10** Implement `HandleCreateCodeInterpreter` handler - POST /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters\n- [ ] **5.11** Implement `HandleGetCodeInterpreter` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}\n- [ ] **5.12** Implement `HandleListCodeInterpreters` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters\n- [ ] **5.13** Implement `HandleUpdateCodeInterpreter` handler - PUT /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}\n- [ ] **5.14** Implement `HandleDeleteCodeInterpreter` handler - DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}\n- [ ] **5.15** Implement `HandleGetCodeInterpreterStatus` handler - GET /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status\n- [ ] **5.16** Implement `HandlePatchCodeInterpreterStatus` handler - PATCH /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status\n- [ ] **5.17** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go`\n- [ ] **5.18** Implement `HandleHealthz` handler - GET /healthz (liveness probe, returns \"ok\")\n- [ ] **5.19** Implement `HandleReadyz` handler - GET /readyz (readiness probe, 200 when ready, 503 when not)\n- [ ] **5.20** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/metrics.go`\n- [ ] **5.21** Implement `HandleMetrics` handler - Prometheus metrics endpoint\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Middleware Implementation\n\n- [ ] **6.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go`\n- [ ] **6.2** Implement `LoggingMiddleware` function - logs method, path, status code, latency\n- [ ] **6.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/error.go`\n- [ ] **6.4** Define error codes constants in `error.go` (ErrCodeInvalidRequest, ErrCodeNotFound, etc.)\n- [ ] **6.5** Implement `ErrorMiddleware` function - map Kubernetes API errors to HTTP status codes\n- [ ] **6.6** Implement `handleAPIError` function - structured error response with message, reason, code\n- [ ] **6.7** Implement `httpStatusForErrorCode` function - error code to HTTP status mapping\n- [ ] **6.8** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go`\n- [ ] **6.9** Implement `CORSMiddleware` function - handle CORS preflight requests\n- [ ] **6.10** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go`\n- [ ] **6.11** Implement `RecoveryMiddleware` function - recover from panics, return 500\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Server Setup & Graceful Shutdown\n\n- [ ] **7.1** Implement `NewServer` constructor function in `server.go`\n- [ ] **7.2** Implement `setupRouter` method in `server.go` - configure Gin router\n- [ ] **7.3** Configure middleware stack (Logging, Recovery, CORS, Error)\n- [ ] **7.4** Implement `RegisterRoutes` method - wire up all route groups\n- [ ] **7.5** Implement `Start` method - start HTTP server with configurable port\n- [ ] **7.6** Implement graceful shutdown logic - stop accepti